parent_collections.title: Standard operating procedure for the isolation of genetically engineered hPSCs clones in a high-throughput way

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6mdr4","text":"Change medium to hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor one day before subcloning ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9ds0e","text":"Wash the genotype-confirmed wells with DPBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bi9l4","text":"Add 25 µl Trypsin to those wells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c32uv","text":"Incubate      ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":10,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":12,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"6hakv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":300,"guid":"49C08DE07DA311ECB567D7C090A77204","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}},"1":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"4B7828F07DA311ECB567D7C090A77204","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"37","unit":10}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6v9b9","text":"Add 75 µl hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor, mix well by pipetting","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ein1b","text":"Transfer dissociated cells to a 15 conical tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5ahgc","text":"Prepare three MEF wells of a 6-well plate. Seed 1/100, 1/1,1000 and the rest of the cells respectively to those wells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e3rv0","text":"Change medium daily for the high density well starting from day 3. Change medium every 3 days for the low density wells in the first week, then every other day in the second week","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a52il","text":"Once the high density wells grow to 50-70% confluency, freeze. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9b3b6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e2l0t","text":"For a detailed protocol on freezing hPSCs, refer to \"Freezing of hPSCs grown on MEFs\" in the \"Thawing, Passaging and Freezing of hPSCs on MEFs\" collection; dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4msqu6e","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3snj8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ccucd","text":"For a detailed protocol on freezing feeder-free hPSCs, refer to \"Freezing of feeder-free hPSCs\" in the \"Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs\" collection; dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4mcqu2w","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a8d2v","text":"When big hPSCs colonies form in the low density wells, change medium to hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"63da","text":"The day after, proceed with manual colony picking","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6qrl6","text":"For each original clone, prepare six microcentrifuge tubes pre-added with 20 µl Trypsin","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"74k66","text":"Aspirate medium and add 2 ml DMEM/F12","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"c5tui","text":"Change medium to DPBS for the well where colonies will be picked ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ke28","text":"Under the dissecting microscope, use mouth pipet or a fine 10 µl tip to pick one undifferentiated colony which is fully separated from other colonies. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"afs25","text":"Transfer the colony to one microcentrifuge tube from step 12. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"95c52","text":"Repeat step 15-16 to pick another five colonies","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7jchd","text":"Incubate the microcentrifuge tubes at     ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":38,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":40,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"j068","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"7FF5D0007DA311ECB567D7C090A77204","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"37","unit":10}},"1":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":300,"guid":"EF9BA2507E1511ECB71F4192B1BA0E47","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bmpk9","text":"Add 70 µl hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor to each tube, pipet to mix","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bo3ql","text":"Seed all cells into one well of a 12-well MEF plate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9j4ae","text":"Shake plates to distribute cells evenly","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"t5v3","text":"Culture for 7-10 days with medium change daily from day 3","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7650h","text":"When the subclones grow to 50-70% confluence, passage and prepare crude cell lysis for NGS genotyping","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2pf9r","text":"Once genotype confirmed, expand and freeze the one subclone, which shows the best hPSCs morphology and proliferates normally. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
